ementation of the program; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15833/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15833/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs15833%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for any State that has adopted a statewide program as of , activities that reduce energy consumption in the State by expanding and improving the program.August 8, 2005","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Verification","label":"b Verification","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15833/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15833","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs15833%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A State that receives financial assistance under subsection (a)(1) shall submit to the Secretary independent verification of any energy savings achieved through the statewide program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"c Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15833/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15833","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs15833%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is authorized to be appropriated to carry out this section $5,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2006 through 2010, to remain available until expended.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
